              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant past medical history. He was born full-term via normal vaginal delivery with no perinatal complications. His immunizations are up to date per the national childhood immunization schedule, including influenza vaccine last autumn. He has had two prior episodes of common cold in previous years, both of which resolved without complications. He has no history of hospitalizations, surgeries, or chronic illnesses such as asthma or allergic rhinitis. He has a known allergy to amoxicillin, which caused a skin rash during treatment for otitis media at age 5. Family history is significant for allergic rhinitis in his mother. {patientName} is not on any regular medications and his developmental milestones are appropriate for his age."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
